The paper deals with the geometry and combinatorics of convex polytopes, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The use of $f$- and $h$-vector calculus and shellings also suggests that it could belong to the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. The paper also deals with upper bounds and tightness of those bounds, which suggests that it could belong to the graph theory (cs.GT) or optimization (cs.MG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the Minkowski sum of convex polytopes, which suggests that it could belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) or the symbolic data analysis (cs.SD) sub-categories.
